In this joint statement, President Obama and President Park Geun-hye express their commitment to countering the threat posed by North Korea's nuclear and ballistic missile programs. They affirm their goal of achieving complete denuclearization of North Korea and urge North Korea to comply with international obligations and commitments. They oppose any actions by North Korea that raise tensions or violate UN Security Council resolutions and warn of consequences if North Korea carries out a nuclear test or missile launch. The statement also emphasizes the importance of dialogue and cooperation with China and other parties to bring North Korea back to meaningful talks. The leaders pledge to never accept North Korea as a nuclear-weapon state and express support for President Park's efforts to improve inter-Korean relations. They condemn the human rights situation in North Korea and commit to working with the international community to improve human rights and livelihoods in the country.